column6: This report includes an un-itemized lump sum receipt of $59,729.94 and itemized individual receipts of $4,050.00. The total, $63,779.94, is comprised of individual receipts intended for an affiliated organization that were mistakenly deposited by a third-party credit card processor into the wrong bank account. Those receipts of $200 and above are itemized with a memo text indicating they were part of the mis-deposited batch. We have transferred the funds out of the PAC account to the affiliate as of 3/17/2021. We are contacting the affected individuals to inform them that their contributions have been moved to the intended account. Per guidance received from FEC, we are disclosing these contributions on the March monthly report and will similarly report a disbursement on the April monthly report.
